# SHOPKEEPER DOMAIN MODEL v1.6

Last Update: 02.03.2026

---

## Core Philosophy

Hybrid architecture:

Retail = Escrow-controlled marketplace  
Wholesale = Public B2B lot exchange  
Wholesale Premium = Manual Escrow Guarantee Module  
Promotion Layer = Paid visibility engine  
Notification Layer = Event-driven user engagement system  
Audit Layer = Immutable state tracking system  

---

# Roles

UserRole:

- buyer
- seller
- trusted_seller
- admin

TrustLevel:

- normal
- trusted
- suspended

Only trusted sellers may be eligible for Premium Guarantee.  
Admin override always possible (audited).

---

# Product (Retail)

Product:

- id: UUID
- sellerId: User.id
- type: retail (system-defined)
- condition: new | used
- title: string
- price: float
- currency: string
- maxQuantityPerOrder: int (required, DB default = 1)
- status: draft | active
- createdAt
- updatedAt

ProductImage:

- id
- productId
- url
- isPrimary
- createdAt

---

## Retail Business Rules (v1 Stable)

1. Product creation allowed only for role = seller
2. price must be > 0
3. currency required
4. condition allowed values: new | used
5. maxQuantityPerOrder required
6. Default status on creation = draft
7. Publication must be separate use-case
8. Used retail requires:
   - at least one image
   - moderation before activation
9. Only seller-owner or admin may publish
10. Publication writes AuditLog event

---

## Retail Lifecycle

draft → active

State transition must go through Service layer.

---

# Order (Escrow Retail)

Order:

- id
- buyerId
- sellerId
- productId
- status:
  - created
  - funds_frozen
  - awaiting_admin_review (future)
  - approved (future)
  - rejected (future)
  - cancelled_by_admin (future)
  - completed (future)
- createdAt
- updatedAt

Payment (future full integration):

- id
- orderId
- amount
- currency
- status:
  - initiated
  - frozen
  - released
  - refunded
  - failed

---

## Order Lifecycle (Escrow Phase 1)

created  
→ funds_frozen  

Rules:

1. Only buyer can create order
2. Buyer cannot buy own product
3. Only active product can be ordered
4. Only buyer can confirm order
5. confirmOrder moves:
   created → funds_frozen
6. Every transition writes AuditLog
7. State transitions only via Service layer

Escrow logic will expand in Phase 2.

---

# Wholesale (Public Lot Exchange)

WholesaleOffer:

- id
- sellerId
- modelName
- condition
- location
- quantityAvailable
- description
- expiresAt
- status:
  - active
  - expired
  - suspended
- createdAt
- updatedAt

WholesalePriceTier:

- id
- wholesaleOfferId
- minQuantity
- pricePerUnit

Rules:

- Auto-expire after 72h
- Public visibility
- No escrow
- No stock reservation
- Max 3 price tiers
- minQuantity increasing
- minQuantity ≤ quantityAvailable
- price decreases or stays equal

---

# Promotion Module

Promotion:

- id
- entityType (product | wholesale)
- entityId
- sellerId
- promotionType:
  - boost
  - featured
  - pinned
- startsAt
- expiresAt
- isActive
- createdAt

Rules:

- Does not modify entity data
- Affects sorting only
- Expired promotions ignored
- Multiple historical records allowed

---

# Notification & Push Module

Notification:

- id
- userId
- type:
  - retail_order_update
  - wholesale_new_lot
  - premium_update
  - seller_new_offer
- title
- message
- relatedEntityType
- relatedEntityId
- isRead
- createdAt

PushSubscription:

- id
- userId
- endpoint
- p256dh
- auth
- deviceType
- createdAt

UserNotificationSettings:

- userId
- retailOrderUpdates
- wholesaleNewLots
- premiumDealUpdates
- modelSubscriptionsEnabled
- sellerSubscriptionsEnabled

ModelSubscription:

- id
- userId
- modelName
- createdAt

SellerSubscription:

- id
- userId
- sellerId
- createdAt

---

# Audit Layer

AuditLog:

- id
- entityType
- entityId
- action
- actorId
- metadata
- createdAt

Rules:

1. Every state transition must generate AuditLog
2. Audit records are immutable
3. Audit never modifies domain data
4. Audit enables:
   - dispute resolution
   - fraud analysis
   - compliance tracking
   - admin investigation

---

# Architectural Rules

1. Business logic exists only in Service layer
2. Repository layer contains zero business logic
3. State transitions are explicit and validated
4. No direct status updates outside Service
5. Escrow logic isolated from Wholesale
6. Promotion never modifies entity data
7. Notification respects user settings
8. Admin override allowed but audited

---

# System Invariants

1. Retail requires maxQuantityPerOrder
2. Retail default status = draft
3. Used retail requires image + moderation
4. Wholesale auto-expires after 72h
5. Standard Wholesale has no escrow
6. Promotion never alters entity data
7. Notification system respects user settings
8. Admin override always audited
9. Order transitions are strictly controlled
10. AuditLog must exist for all critical actions